2 SENATE BILL 700
1 This title applies only in Wicomico County.
2 32–1003.
3 (a) There is a Class B beer, wine, and liquor (golf course) license.
4 (b) The Board of License Commissioners may issue the license for the use of a golf
5 course or organization that:
6 (1) is open to the public;
7 (2) is operated for profit;
8 (3) owns real estate in the county; and
9 (4) has a golf course with a minimum of 18 holes.
10 (c) (1) The license holder may sell beer, wine, and liquor for consumption on
11 the land and in the buildings, including the clubhouse, used for golfing purposes.
12 (2) A patron need not be seated to be served.
13 (d) A holder of the license may sell beer, wine, and liquor:
14 (1) on Monday through Saturday, from [10 a.m.] 7 A.M. to 2 a.m. the
15 following day; and
16 (2) on Sunday, from [10 a.m.] 7 A.M. to midnight.
17 (e) The annual license fee is $2,200.
18 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
19 1, 2026.
Approved:
